.TH HSH 1 "August 2025" "hsh 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- HSH - SIMPLE SHELL
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ script ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBhsh\fP is a simple UNIX-like command line interpreter. It can run in
interactive mode with a prompt, or in non-interactive mode when a script
or input is provided through standard input.

Commands can be either built-in or external programs found in the PATH
environment variable. Exit statuses follow standard UNIX conventions.

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are implemented:

.TP
.B exit
Terminate the shell, returning the last command exit status.

.TP
.B env
Display the current environment, one variable per line.

.TP
Additional builtins may be implemented.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of \fBhsh\fP is the exit status of the last executed command.
If a command cannot be found, the shell returns 127.
If a command terminates due to a signal, the exit status is 128 plus the signal number.

.SH EXAMPLES
Run interactively:
.EX
$ hsh
($) ls -l
($) env
($) exit
.EE

Run a script:
.EX
$ echo "ls -l" > script.sh
$ ./hsh script.sh
.EE

Error when command not found:
.EX
($) foobar
hsh: 1: foobar: not found
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2), fork(2), waitpid(2)

